    "id": 30,
    "title": "Quick Guide for High Quality Backlinks",
    "slug": "quick-guide-for-high-quality-backlinks",
    "excerpt": "Quick Guide for High Quality Backlinks",
    "content": "<div class=\"entry-content clear\" itemprop=\"text\">\n<h4><span style=\"color: #000000;\">High Quality vs Low Quality Backlinks</span></h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">We already read tons about low-quality backlinks and unnatural backlinks. What about the high-quality ones? These are those that get your site upper and upper within the SERPs, so let&rsquo;s focus for a moment and see what&rsquo;s so different between a high-quality link versus a traditional link.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From the purpose of jumping into a replacement business and landing on the primary page in program results, there&rsquo;s an extended way.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The SEO land is filled with bad tips for getting backlinks from spammy websites and dealing with shady SEO consultant which will bring your site in no time on the primary page.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Which is essentially impossible to try to do in brief amount of time, if you would like to grow your backlinks profile naturally.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From a generic point of view the overall important characteristics of a top-quality link are:</span></p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Domain Authority</span></h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If an important domain has backlinks to your site, there&rsquo;s a good chance that your website has something important to mention in your niche, similar to real life, if an important person mentions you, the impression of the listeners will be influenced by his high authority in the field.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">That way your importance will grow and it can bring a rise in organic traffic, conversion rate.</span></p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Relevance</span></h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A relevant backlink is a link that is positioned on a site/page that talks about the same subject, or is in the same niche with your site. The relevance of a link may be given based on the content of the linking site or page and the contextual relevance of the words surrounding the link.</span></p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Uniqueness</span></h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A high-quality link has even more power, if it&rsquo;s hard for your competitors to get a natural link from the same source. Links from relevant and authority sites that only talk about your website and not your competitors can be considered great link opportunities because they are unique to your site.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A quick example of such a link, would be conference sites that link to the companies and speakers that are participating at that conference.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Naturally, not all your competitors can be present at that conference so that is a great place to build some high quality and unique links to your site.</span></p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Traffic</span></h4>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If a link isn&rsquo;t clicked, then the initial purpose of the link is voided. it&rsquo;s important to have your link during a visible place on the positioning so that people click it and thus drive traffic to your site. for example, footer links can&rsquo;t be considered important as they&rsquo;re only seen by search engine crawlers and are rarely clicked by people.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">A footer link on a popular domain such as <a style=\"color: #000000;\" href=\"http://quora.com/\">Quora</a> can have a major influence on your site and it can help you improve your rankings.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">On the opposite hand, multiple footer backlinks to your website from sites that connected with one another can bring you a Google Penguin penalty.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From a technical point of view, Model the properties of a high-quality link which are as follows:</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;Authority of domain</span></h5>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From a High Authority Referring Domain.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Linking Domain Ranks Well in Google.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Linking Domain features a lot of Referring Domains.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;Relevance of page/site</span></h5>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In the Same Niche as your site</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Links mostly to content within the same niche.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; &nbsp;Uniqueness in terms of website</span></h5>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Does not link to all of your competitors.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Links to Informational sources mostly.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; Website traffic and visibility</span></h5>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Has a Big Number of visitors?</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Has a lively Readership. (if it&rsquo;s a blog)</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Has Good Social Media Exposure.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp; Other Important Properties</span></h5>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In-Content Link. (from a blog or content page)</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Few Links on the Linking Page.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The Site Links only to Relevant Content.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Non-Commercial Anchor Text Rich.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Non-Sponsored.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">All of the aspects mentioned above fall under the white hat SEO tactics and this suggests it respects Google&rsquo;s Quality Guidelines.</span></p>\n</div>",
